  "text": "Experimental procedures conformed to institutional guidelines for the care and use of animals in research. Detailed methodology is contained in the online data supplement, available at http://www. circresaha.org. Hibernating myocardium was produced in pigs by chronic instrumentation of the left anterior descending artery (LAD) with a 1.5-mm (ID) Delrin stenosis, as previously described. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] Studies were conducted in 16 chronically instrumented animals and in 15 normal controls under isoflurane (1% to 3%) anesthesia supplemented with Telazol (tiletamine/zolazepam)/xylazine (Fort Dodge Animal Health, Fort Dodge, Iowa; IM every 30 to 60 minutes).",
